        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 5:12PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Bella Vista, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Garfield...                       Rogers...
Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...Hill Top...
Walnut Hill...                    Vaughn...
Bentonville...                    Hiwasse...
Pea Ridge...                      Avoca...
Miller...                         Bella Vista...
Centerton...                      Highfill...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 83 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
